content: This is such a good find and after all these years is still strong and addictive. Playable one handed and lots of depth to be discovered once you start to go deep. By the way - just found out you can stand up on tiptoes... sometimes useful to collect gems above you.

I do believe Doug Dug is my favorite mobile game. The developers hit it out 
of the park with this game. First of all, refreshingly, NO IN GAME ADS OR 
PURCHASES! Thank you! This is a solid, well thought out game with many 
lovely small details that set it apart. Fun, realistic physics, difficulty 
curve increases just right as you progress deeper and deeper, and I love 
the retro graphics. I'm addicted enough where I've finally hit the $1 
million mark with my best game. Love this game!

Edit: I still play this game from time to time. One of my all time favorites android games!!   Move Doug around. Dig. Don't die. Absolute best use of the mobile format. More games need to be like this.

Too often are mobile games built upon pay-to-win game models. This game does mobile correctly: make a fun, simple, charming game that keeps you coming back but doesn't force you to go through pay/time walls. Good controls, nice aesthetics,  and addictive game play. Other developers should take note when it comes to making mobile games. This doesn't even have annoying ads in it.

What I really love about this game is the way cave-ins happen. Different dirt blocks seem to have different strength and weight, so figuring out what will or will not collapse is always fun. ------ just updating my review to say how well this game holds up under a lot of play. In all this time I have not gotten tired of it. Doug Dug remains one of my very favorite Android games. Thank you for making it!

A few minor niggles prevent this being 5* for me - it badly needs Google Play achievements and leaderboards and immersive mode would be great.  FInally it would be nice if there was a little more...er..depth to it - for instance, if the treasure collected could be used to buy powerups or equipment between games.  Still for less than 60p this is a total no-brainer.  Buy it.

I've been waiting for Namco to port Mr. Driller over to Android for some time now, but gave up.  Now, it seems someone's wised up and made their own version (minus the need for oxygen).  But to me, it doesn't feel much like a clone.  Don't be put off by the graphics if you're new to old school gaming, this game has loads of gameplay and replay value that'll have you come for more.  It also takes a bit strategy, like avoiding enemies and falling earth that sometimes randomly breaks away from above.  Like I said, it's reminiscent of Mr. Driller and Dig Dug, so that's a good thing.  The game feels different every time you play it because it's randomly generated (or at least it looks like it is), which is good.  I think that any retro game fan will "dig" the threads this game is wearing (ha-ha).  On top of everything else, it's light weight; a little more than 8mb.  I've seen games with minimal graphics and sounds like this topping at a whopping 30-40mb, for whatever reason.  So if you have a phone that doesn't allow you to move apps to SD card (which sucks, cuz I used to have one), you're good on this one player.  Now play on!
